# CEO Report: Memory System Overhaul
Date: 2026-04-08
Project: YVON Session System Optimization
DRI: 💻 Dev Lead (with Raj Backend + Mia Frontend support)
Status: ✅ SHIPPED

---

## Executive Summary

The Problem:
SIP triggering required manual detection — agents didn't know when distillation was due
File growth unmanaged — MEMORY.md files growing without bounds
Cross-file dependencies — 31+ files referenced SESSION.md directly, creating tight coupling

The Solution:
Implemented 4-phase automation system with:
Centralized Session Manager service
Automated SIP scheduling and notification
Smart memory management with caps and compression
Enhanced agent collaboration with routing intelligence

The Result:
✅ 17/17 validation tests passed
✅ 22 MEMORY.md files optimized
✅ Centralized session management
✅ Automated SIP workflows
✅ Enhanced agent collaboration

---

## Phase 1: Session Manager Foundation ✅

### What Was Built
lib/session-manager.ts — Centralized service for SESSION.md operations
lib/session-schema.ts — Zod schema validation and migration utilities

### Key Features
Singleton pattern — Single instance manages all SESSION.md operations
Schema validation — Validates format and provides migration path
Change listeners — Agents can subscribe to SESSION.md updates
Type safety — Full TypeScript types for all session data

### Files Changed
[TABLE:2×3]

### Test Results
✅ Session Manager can read SESSION.md
✅ Session data has required structure
✅ SESSION.md validation passes
✅ SESSION.md migration adds schema version

---

## Phase 2: SIP Automation System ✅

### What Was Built
lib/sip-manager.ts — SIP triggering, scheduling, and execution
app/api/sip/run/route.ts — API endpoint for manual SIP execution

### Key Features
Automated triggering — Every 5 sessions triggers SIP automatically
Agent notification — SIP flags appear in agent's MEMORY.md
Priority system — Low/Medium/High based on age
Report generation — Get pending and overdue SIPs

### Files Changed
[TABLE:2×3]

### Test Results
✅ Get Pending SIPs works
✅ Generate SIP Report works
✅ SIP Manager functions imported correctly

---

## Phase 3: Memory Management System ✅

### What Was Built
lib/memory-manager.ts — MEMORY.md optimization and management

### Key Features
Multi-section caps — Different limits per section (50/100/50/30/20)
Compression logic — Old entries compressed after 30-90 days
Archive system — Entries >90 days moved to archive files
Section statistics — Get detailed stats on memory usage

### Files Changed
[TABLE:2×2]

### Optimization Results
[CODE::4LOC]

### Test Results
✅ Archive directory exists
✅ Section stats generated correctly
✅ All 22 MEMORY.md files found and optimized

